The EU is reportedly readying "effective and comprehensive" ammunition to respond to disagreements with the UK, according to European Commission. An EU official told Channel 4 News that readying the tools for a rapid EU response would be a "useful message to pass to the United Kingdom" right now following the British Government's decision to pass legislation that would allow them to unilaterally remove parts of the Northern Ireland Protocol. The EU measures are expected to be broad enough to allow the EU to act unilaterally in response "to defend its interest." THIS LIVE BLOG IS NOW CLOSED.